<h2><a name="abs" id="abs">abs</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdlib&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> abs<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">int</span> num <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>

The abs() function returns the absolute value of num. For example:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">     <span class="kw4">int</span> magic_number <span class="sy0">=</span> <span class="nu0">10</span>;
     <a href="http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/cout.html"><span class="kw3">cout</span></a> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;Enter a guess: &quot;</span>;
     cin <span class="sy0">&gt;&gt;</span> x;
     <a href="http://www.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/009695399/functions/cout.html"><span class="kw3">cout</span></a> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="st0">&quot;Your guess was &quot;</span> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> abs<span class="br0">&#40;</span> magic_number <span class="sy0">-</span> x <span class="br0">&#41;</span> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> <span class="st0">&quot; away from the
  magic number.&quot;</span> <span class="sy0">&lt;&lt;</span> endl;</pre>
<p>
C++ also provides the following overloaded forms:

</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstdlib&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> abs<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">long</span> num <span class="br0">&#41;</span>; <span class="co1">// same as labs()</span>
&nbsp;
    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="co1">// the following are synonyms for fabs()</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> abs<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">float</span> num <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
    <span class="kw4">double</span> abs<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> num <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> abs<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> num <span class="br0">&#41;</span>;</pre>
<p>
Related Topics: <a href="fabs" class="wikilink1" title="c:math:fabs">fabs</a>, <a href="labs" class="wikilink1" title="c:math:labs">labs</a>
</p>

